# Copy this file to user.bazelrc (already gitignored) and adjust paths.
#
# ── Disk cache ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Persists build artifacts across clean builds, branch switches, and Bazel
# version upgrades.  After the first full build, unchanged targets are served
# from cache (near-instant).  ~5-20 GB typical size; Bazel evicts old entries
# automatically.
#
# Replace /Users/YOURNAME with your actual home directory (~ is not expanded).
#
build --disk_cache=/Users/YOURNAME/.cache/bazel-telegram-ios
#
# ── Reduce index overhead for pure CLI / CI builds ───────────────────────────
# Uncomment to skip Xcode source indexing (saves ~10-15% on non-Xcode builds):
#
# build --features=-swift.index_while_building
# build --features=-swift.use_global_index_store
#
# ── Override batch mode thread count ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Default is -j4 (set in .bazelrc).  Lower this if you need the machine
# responsive while building (e.g. -j2 leaves 2 CPUs free):
#
# build --swiftcopt=-j2
